<h1>Problem 2181 - 2018 IZHO, P2 of 6, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>Let \(N\), \(K\), \(L\) be points on sides \(AB\), \(BC\), \(CA\) respectively such that \(CN\) is the bisector of \(\angle ACB\) and \(AL=BK\). The segments \(AK\) and \(BL\) meet at \(P\). Let \(I\), \(J\) be the incenters of triangles \(\triangle BPK\) and \(\triangle ALP\) respectively. If \(IJ\) and \(CN\) meet at \(Q\), prove that \(IQ =JP\).</p>
